# AbiDocker

Docker containers for building and testing [ABINIT](https://www.abinit.org/) — atomic-scale simulation software based on density functional theory (DFT).



## Available Configurations

| Configuration | Status | Image Size | Use Case |
|---|---|---|---|
| **minimal-serial** | ✅ | ~500 MB | Learning, testing, CI/CD |
| **mpi-openblas** | ✅ | ~1.5 GB | Production parallel calculations |
| **Intel MKL** | 🚧 | ~2–3 GB | HPC with Intel compilers |
| **GPU (CUDA/ROCm)** | 🚧 | ~8–12 GB | GPU-accelerated calculations |

## Quick Start

```bash
# Build minimal-serial (no MPI, single-core)
./scripts/build-all.sh minimal-serial

# Build MPI + OpenBLAS (parallel)
./scripts/build-all.sh mpi-openblas

# Run the H2 example calculation
./examples/run-abinit.sh

# Interactive shell in container
./scripts/test-container.sh minimal-serial
```

**Prerequisites**: Docker, 10+ GB disk, 4+ GB RAM for Docker. Build time: ~20–40 min.

## Custom ABINIT Sources

```bash
# Specific version
export ABINIT_BRANCH=9.10.3
./scripts/build-all.sh minimal-serial

# From a fork
export ABINIT_REPO=https://github.com/yourfork/abinit.git
export ABINIT_BRANCH=feature-branch
./scripts/build-all.sh minimal-serial
```

Build arguments: `ABINIT_REPO`, `ABINIT_BRANCH`, `RUN_TESTS` (`yes`/`no`), `TEST_SUITE` (`fast`/`paral`).

## Running ABINIT

```bash
# Basic calculation
docker run --rm -v $(pwd):/workspace \
  abidocker/abinit:minimal-serial \
  abinit input.in

# With OpenMP threading
docker run --rm -e OMP_NUM_THREADS=4 -v $(pwd):/workspace \
  abidocker/abinit:minimal-serial \
  abinit input.in

# Extract test results
docker run --rm abidocker/abinit:minimal-serial \
  cat /opt/abinit/test-results/test.log
```

## Build Scripts

| Script | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `scripts/build-all.sh` | Build one or more configurations |
| `scripts/build-config.sh` | Build a single configuration with options |
| `scripts/build-matrix.sh` | Build multiple configs (parallel capable) |
| `scripts/test-container.sh` | Run and test containers interactively |
| `scripts/ci/validate-build.sh` | Full CI validation pipeline |

```bash
# Build with tests
./scripts/build-all.sh --run-tests mpi-openblas

# Build specific branch, skip cache
./scripts/build-all.sh --no-cache --branch 9.10.3 minimal-serial

# CI validation
./scripts/ci/validate-build.sh minimal-serial
```

## Project Structure

```
abidocker/
├── .github/workflows/build-test.yml  # CI/CD pipeline
├── AGENTS.md                         # AI agent guidelines
├── CONTRIBUTING.md                   # Development guidelines
├── CHANGELOG.md                      # Version history
├── dockerfiles/
│   ├── .dockerignore
│   ├── common/install-deps.sh        # Shared dependency functions
│   ├── minimal-serial/               # ✅ No MPI, netlib BLAS/LAPACK
│   └── mpi-openblas/                 # ✅ OpenMPI, OpenBLAS, ScaLAPACK
├── scripts/                          # Build, test, CI scripts
├── docs/
│   ├── BUILD_REQUIREMENTS.md         # Platform & dependency guide
│   └── DOCKER_USAGE.md               # Detailed Docker usage
└── examples/
    ├── run-abinit.sh                 # Example runner
    └── simple-calculation/           # H2 molecule test case
```

## CI/CD

GitHub Actions workflow at `.github/workflows/build-test.yml` builds both configurations in parallel on push/PR to `main` or `master`. Requires `DOCKER_USERNAME` and `DOCKER_TOKEN` secrets for registry push.

## Troubleshooting

- **Build fails**: Ensure 10+ GB disk, 4+ GB Docker RAM. Check logs: `docker build ... 2>&1 | tee build.log`
- **Tests fail**: Some failures expected with minimal config. Skip with `--build-arg RUN_TESTS=no`
- **OOM**: Reduce system size in input, lower `OMP_NUM_THREADS`, increase Docker memory

